The Niger State Universal Basic Education Board (NSUBEB) has made public the list of 2,510 teachers and 320 unskilled staff recruited by the state government to boost the deficit of teachers in primary schools across the state. The statement enjoined all applicants who sat for the written and oral examinations to check their names in their various local government areas across the state from tomorrow 25/10/2019. The statement signed by the public relations officer of the Board comrade Idris Kolo added that the appointment will take effect from 2nd November 2019 and urged all the successful applicants to collect their offer of appointment and commence documentation immediately.  ...to resume work next month ...spent over N6b on Education in six years. By Wole Mosadomi Niger State government has recruited 2,500 new teachers and are expected to resume work across the State next month. The recruitment was spread across the three Senatorial District of the State and those finally… October 16, 2019 In "Education" Many residents of Niger State believe the development of capital projects  executed across the state by Gov Abubakar Sani Bello have  endorsed him for another term ahead of next year’s  general elections. September 22, 2018 In "News" NIGER State governor, Alhaji Abubakar Sani Bello, has directed the immediate forensic audit of the contributory pension scheme, CPS in the state. May 3, 2017 In "News"